Colin de Grandhomme is stationed there but he is standing few metres ahead of the boundary fence making it difficult for him to reach it on time.
Full delivery outside off, Starc drives this to cover and picks up a single.
Flatter delivery on middle, Tim defends it out of the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Starc pushes it back towards the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Starc defends it off the front foot.
Short delivery on off, Starc cuts it through point. The batsmen take a single.
Floated delivery on off, Paine plays it towards point. The batsmen cross ends.
Tossed up delivery on off, Mitchell defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nice shot. Loopy delivery on middle, Starc plays a slog sweep over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length delivery on middle, Paine flicks it through square leg. The batsmen take a single.
On a good length on middle, Starc defends it off the back foot.
Short delivery outside off, Starc cuts it through point for a run.

FOUR! STOP THE PRESS! Tim Paine has scored a boundary. It has been a yawning session of batting from Australia, led by their skipper. That is just his second boundary in the 98 balls that he has faced. Nice shot though. On a length, outside off, Paine rocks back and punches it late, behind point. Sweeper cover is there but before he can sweep across, the ball meets the fence.
Outside off, Paine lets it go.
Good length delivery on off, Paine defends it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Starc defends it off the front foot.
Short on off, Starc slaps it towards covers. The batsmen take a single.

'I AM SORRY!' says Starc. Floated delivery on middle, Paine drives it towards mid on. Santner dives to his right but cannot stop the ball. Now, Paine comes halfway down the track for the single but Starc is busy looking at the mid on fielder. Now he looks back at Paine who indicates that it was his call and he should have run.
Full delivery on off, Paine drives it towards mid off for a run.

SIX! WHACK! Making hay while the sun shines. Starc is getting into the groove. Full and around off, plenty of flight. Starc gets down and slogs it over long on. There is a fielder over there but no problem. Mitch has enough power. 400 UP FOR AUSTRALIA.
Floated delivery on off, Mitchell plays it towards point for a single.
Bowls a bouncer, Starc ducks under it.
Length delivery on off, Starc plays it towards mid off.
On a good length on off, Starc defends it to point off the back foot.

DROPPED! When it is not going, it is definitely not going for you. Jeet Raval has been having a torrid time with the bat and now, drops a sitter. Is the possible declaration going on in his mind? Length delivery on middle, Starc looks to loft but hits it straight to mid on. Jeet Raval tries to take the catch, gets to it but then spills it.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Starc looks to cut but misses it.
Outside off, Mitchell leaves it alone.
Full delivery on off, Paine drives it towards mid off. The fielder goes for a direct hit at the bowler's end but misses it. The batsmen manage to take a single.
Bowls a bouncer, Starc lets it sail through to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Starc drives it back towards the bowler.
On a length on off, Starc guides it to short third man.
Full delivery on off, Starc plays it back towards the bowler.
Full again on middle, Starc looks to flick but gets an inside edge. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen cross ends.
Outside off, Starc offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on leg, Starc looks to flick but misses it and gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
WIDE! Bowls a bouncer outside off, Starc lets it sail through to the keeper. The umpire gives it wide for height.
Length delivery on off, Starc lofts it over covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Full delivery on off, Starc drives it back towards the bowler.
Outside off, Starc shoulders arms to this one.

OUT! Caught! Starc holes out now. Finally someone is there to take a catch. Great take from a great player. Kane Williamson. After spending 145 overs in the field, you do this. Rephrase. EVEN after spending so much time on the field, you do this. Full and outside off, angling away, Starc looks to go over the bowler but the bat turns in his hands and he ends up skewing it. The ball goes off the top edge high in the air. It looks like it will land safely but Williamson covers good ground to his right from mid off, keeps his eyes on the ball and then slides to take a stunner. Superb. Starc's cameo ends but the innings doesn't. Australia continue to bat.
Full delivery on off, Lyon defends it back towards the bowler.
Full delivery on off again, Lyon keeps it out.
FOUR! Good shot. Short delivery on leg, Lyon pulls it over square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Nathan Lyon. Short of a length delivery on leg, Lyon pulls it over fine leg for a boundary.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Lyon looks to drive but misses it.

OUT! Caught! That is a good catch from Colin de Grandhomme and Wagner has his fourth! A short ball, outside leg, from over the wicket, Lyon looks to pull but this time gets a bit of a top edge. The ball flies in the air and de Grandhomme at fine leg slides to his right and takes a good catch as the ball was coming at pace.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery. On a good length and just outside off, Paine looks to defend but misses it.

OUT! Caught behind! No 5-fer for Wagner, no declaration from Australia because they have been bowled out. A short ball, down the leg side, Paine looks to pull but he is cramped for room. The ball takes the glove and BJ Watling dives to his left to take the catch. He appeals and umpire Aleem Dar raises his finger. Paine does not bother reviewing and the innings ends at last. 416 IS WHAT AUSTRALIA HAVE MANAGED. TEA AS WELL ON DAY 2.
Starts off with a very full delivery on middle, no swing on offer for Starc. Raval is solid in defense as he shows the full face of the bat.
A little too straight and the length is also shorter. Raval looks to leave it but is hit on the thigh pad.
Raval is underway! A little too straight again, Raval looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. It rolls on the leg side and a single is taken.
Good delivery and well played in the end! Shorter and on off, it keeps rising after bouncing. Latham does well to pull his bat out of the way right at the end.

OUT! In the air... taken! Latham is out of here for a duck! Now, now, now, who expected that? Everyone would have put his money on Jeet Raval to go early. Mitchell Starc draws first blood. The extra bounce does Latham in. It is shorter and on the body, Latham looks to work it on the leg side but there is extra bounce. He does try to take his hand off the handle but too late. It hits the higher part and lobs back towards the bowler. He takes a dolly moving to his right. An early breakthrough, just the start Australia wanted. Also, a good wicket as Latham is known to play long innings.

A huge shout by Paine but not given! Down the leg side, Williamson looks to flick but misses. There is a sound as the ball passes the batter. Paine takes it and appeals but Starc is not interested. Replay shows it is off the thigh pad. End of a successful first for Starc.

OHHH! That is pretty close. This starts outside off and it comes back in late. Raval lets it be and it goes just over the off pole. He may have not expected it to come back so much but in the end it turned out to be a good leave.
This one is outside off again but it does not come back in. Easy leave.
Closer to the off pole than the last ball, not close enough to make the batter play though.

OUT! KABOOM! Number two is down in the second over itself! So Raval does go early and has been knocked over. Hazlewood too has a wicket to his name. Gets the line right, gets the length right and that is the end of Raval. It is fuller and around middle and off. It tails back in late. Raval fails to adjust to the movement. He tries to flick it in the end but misses. It hits the pads and then the stumps. Another low score for Raval and New Zealand are in big trouble here.
Good delivery first up to Taylor. Made him play. On a length and around off, it is kept out.
Another length delivery around off, Taylor guides it towards point, he wanted a run but is sent back. A dot means it is a wicket maiden from JH. Australia bowlers could have not started any better.
Crisp drive but for no runs! Fuller and on off, Williamson strokes it right off the middle but towards short cover.
Drags his length back this time and it is outside off, Williamson does not fiddle with it.
Good running! Shorter and on off, Williamson stands tall and drops it towards cover and takes one.
Gets this one to shape back in from outside off, Taylor looks to defend but once again there is extra bounce, it hits the splice and rolls towards point.

Nasty stuff from Starc! The Aussies have their tails up here. This is a sharp short one, probably first of this innings. Catches Taylor by surprise. He fails to get out of the way and hits him around the shoulder. A nasty bumper to push the batter up and now a yorker to follow it up?

NOT OUT! Taylor is well in. However, the Kiwi players and the supporters must have had their heart in their mouth. A big mix-up. Starc does not follow the bouncer with a yorker but he bowls it full and it tails back in from off. Taylor works it to the right of Cummins at short mid on and takes off. PC dives to his right and stops it. Seeing that Williamson sends Taylor back who is halfway down the track. Cummins lobs it towards the stumps at the striker's end. He misses but Warner from gully rushes towards the stumps, catches the throw and then underarms it onto the stumps. An appeal and the umpire takes it upstairs. Australia are confident but Taylor seems relaxed. And now we know why as Taylor has his bat grounded.
A length ball, down the leg side, Williamson looks to tuck it to the leg side but the ball hits his gloves and lobs to the leg side. But no short leg in place!
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

FOUR! Off the inside edge, misses the stumps! Streaky. Cummins almost strikes first ball. A length ball, around off, Williamson looks to defend but the ball snakes in, takes the inside edge and flies over the stumps to the fine leg fence!

IN THE AIR... DOES NOT CARRY TO SHORT LEG! A length ball, around middle, Williamson hops across to tuck it to the leg side but is cramped for room. The ball bounces extra, pings the gloves and drops in front of short leg.
This time Willy gets well behind the line of the ball and blocks it.
Back of a length outside off, blocked back to the bowler.

Williamson just saves a boundary! Confused about what I just wrote? I'll explain. Starc goes fuller and on off, Taylor creams it right off the middle towards Williamson at the other end. It was so nicely struck that Kane had no time to move and is hit on the body. That was a certain boundary. Starc too is having a laugh. No damage to Williamson though.
On middle, Taylor hops and works it to mid-wicket.

No short leg and Taylor picks up a run! Not sure though if that would have gone to hand. Another short one and once again Taylor is caught off guard. He looks to fend at it by taking his eyes off the ball. It hits the glove, goes uppishly on the leg side and towards fine leg for one. Probably a short leg should be in place as Starc is getting the ball to bounce really nicely.

An ambitious shout but not given! This is on the pads, Williamson looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The Aussies might just appeal at every given opportunity against Williamson as he is the biggest wicket in this Kiwi line-up.
This time Williamson connects with the flick shot but straight to square leg.

Another superb bumper to end! It is short and on middle, Williamson picks it late. He initially looks to fend at it but then ducks under it in time. Paine takes it with both hands upwards. Another good over comes to an end by Starc.
Beaten on the inside! This lands outside off and it comes back in. Taylor looks to defend outside the line but is beaten all ends up. This is fast bowling at its best from the Aussie pacers.

EDGY BOUNDARY! Full marks to the bowler here but runs for the batters. This is another length delivery around off, it straightens a touch after pitching. Taylor looks to defend but it goes off the outer half through backward point and into the third man fence.

An appeal but too high! Cummins lands one more delivery on a length and around off, it jags back in. Taylor once again is done by the inward movement. He misses the defensive stroke and is hit high on the pads. Ball Tracker confirms it is going over.
Once again awkwardly played! Taylor is living dangerously out there! Another short one and Taylor once again has problems. He somehow fends at it, it goes away from the short leg fielder for one.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

Almost drags it on! Every ball it seems like Australia are going to pick a wicket. Cummins bangs this one shorter in length. Williamson fails to get on top of the bounce. He tries to defend but gets an inside edge which goes close past the leg pole. Another testing over comes to an end.
Three! Shorter and slightly outside off, Williamson hits it hard into the ground. It goes over the leaping point fielder. Warner from gully, hares after it and keeps it down to three.

FOUR! Bread and butter stuff! Fuller and angling away from the batter. Williamson waits for it and just opens the face at the very end. Uses the pace of the ball and guides it through point for a boundary.

Good length and on off, Williamson plays it late and right under his eyes towards gully. That was trademark Williamson. You get a feeling, once he starts playing this defensive stroke nicely, he is at his best.
One more short one on middle, Williamson stands tall and defends it onto the ground.
Outside off and it is left alone.
Probably the first wayward delivery by the Aussies in this innings. Way too short and way too wide outside off. Left alone.
Starts off with an absolute gem! Almost unplayable! This is fuller and on off, it seams away late. Taylor is drawn into the drive but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Bangs it short and on the body, Taylor ducks under it.

FOUR! This time Wade does not get away with the short one. It is on the body of Taylor. Not going to trouble him at that pace, Taylor pulls it through backward square leg and gets a boundary to his name.
Angled into the batter, Taylor works it to mid-wicket.
Slips this one down the leg side, Taylor looks to flick but misses.
Very full ball around off, Taylor guides it through point and gets to the other end. So except for the first ball, it was quite an ordinary over.
A single! Fuller and on middle, Taylor hits it past the bowler towards mid off for one.
Fullish and outside off, tempting Williamson to play a drive. Kane makes another leave.
Another one on the off pole, Williamson is solid in defense.
FOUR! Tickled nice and fine! On the pads, Williamson plays it late and gets it to the fine leg fence. Runs starting to come now.
Shorter and around off, Williamson plays it right onto the ground off the back foot.

Play and a miss! Shorter in length and outside off, Williamson initially looks to push at it but pulls his bat back in time. Now then, Snicko just shows that there was a spike as the ball passes the bat. Also, replays show that Smith was very interested, he did hear something but since the rest weren't sure, no review was taken. That could be a big miss. Williamson could really make Australia pay here especially with them being a bowler down.
Unplayable! Once again the first ball is a jaffa! It initially angles into the off pole which means the batter has to play at it. It pitches and straightens. Beats the outside edge of Taylor's bat.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Length delivery on off, the skipper plays it towards point for a run.
Full delivery on middle, Taylor flicks it towards square leg for a run.
On a good length on off, Kane defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Taylor drives it towards covers where Wade makes a fine stop.
Full again on off, Taylor looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes towards the slip region.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Taylor looks to cut but misses it.
Good length delivery on middle, Taylor rises on his toes and defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Taylor offers no shot to this one.
Bowls a bouncer, Taylor looks to pull but misses it.
Gets this one to turn back in but it is a little too short. Williamson has enough time to go back and push it towards cover.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! A little too full this time from Lyon. It is outside off, Williamson reaches out for it, gets his front foot to the pitch of the ball and creams it through covers.
Flatter and on off, KW goes back and defends it.
Quicker and outside off, Williamson offers no shot to this one.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
One more dot to end! On middle, KW flicks it to the man at mid-wicket. A harmless first by Lyon, he was probably a little too short in this over.
This is angled into the pads, Taylor works it wide of the fielder at mid on and takes one.
Well bowled! In the corridor of uncertainty. Williamson looks to defend but is beaten as he does so inside the line.
On middle, Williamson stays back and works it to mid on.
Outside off again, it is not played at.
Shorter and on middle, KW ducks under it in time.
Shorter and around off, Williamson keeps it out nicely.
Tossed up delivery on off, Taylor defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery outside off, Ross shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Full delivery outside off, Taylor drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
Floated delivery on middle, Taylor defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Taylor keeps it out.
Full delivery on middle, Ross blocks it well.
Slightly shorter and on off, Williamson hops and keeps it out.

Ouch! That might have hurt! Williamson seems in a little pain. This lands on off and it is on a length. Comes back in. Williamson looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the box. Not a pleasant 45 minutes for him. Earlier, he was hit in the same region by a shot from Ross Taylor. Williamson takes a breather but he is fine now.
Shorter in length and on off, Williamson defends it right onto the ground.
Back of a length and outside off, Williamson pushes it towards the man at point. The two somewhat look comfortable now.
Outside off, not played at.
Angled into the pads, Williamson works it to mid-wicket.

In the air... wide! Taylor was rooted to his crease there. It lands outside off and comes back in. Taylor stays inside the crease and tries to defend. It takes the inside edge and then the pads but falls short of the diving short leg fielder.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
FOUR! Just wide! Taylor takes the aggressive approach. He comes down the track, gets to the pitch of it and hits it uppishly. Just wide of the diving mid off fielder and into the fence.
On off, kept out.

FOUR! Up and over! Once again uses the feet to good effect. He gets to the pitch of it. Takes the aerial route, does not hit it that well but clears mid off and bags another boundary. So that inside edge on the first ball is the catalyst for Taylor adopting an aggressive approach. Not wanting to let the offie settle down.

FOUR! Third boundary in the over! This is deft by Taylor. It is quicker and shorter outside off, RT waits for it and guides it past first slip and into the fence. 50 up for the Kiwis. Also, that is the 50-run stand between the two. The best New Zealand pair comes to the fore again. They need to keep going though. They are still 363 runs behind.

FOUR! Oops! Steven Smith is on the ground and laughing. He has slipped. Outside off, Williamson dabs it towards third man. Smith races after it but cannot pull it off. He dives beyond the boundary and then tries to get up but slips. The crowd has a laugh and Smith joins in too.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Back of a length outside off, defended from the crease.
A bouncer on middle, Kane ducks.
Full and around off, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Shorter and outside off, Taylor guides it to point.
Floats it up on off, Taylor strokes it towards cover. The fielder dives to his left and makes a half stop. Two taken.
Flatter and on middle, Taylor pushes it to mid on. Once again Lyon is a little too short.

Well bowled! This is floated up on off, it goes on with the around the wicket angle. Taylor looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge down towards third man for two. This is the advantage of bowling from around the wicket, both the edges come into play.
Down the leg side, Taylor lets it be. Paine does not collect it and it goes down to fine leg. A bye taken.
A single to end! This is tossed up on middle, Williamson hits it down to long on for one.
On a length and around off, it comes at an awkward height for Paine who fails to collect it. Hits him on the finger.

FOUR! Too easy for Williamson! Full and wide outside off, Williamson opens the face of the bat and hits it through cover-point for a boundary. He eases into the stroke, very elegant and pleasing to the eye to watch him play that.
Brilliant comeback from Starc! This lands on off and it is on a length. It pitches and moves away. Williamson is squared up as he tries to defend. Gets beaten.
This is wider outside off, not played at.
On the shorter side again, Williamson nudges it on the leg side.
A couple! A full toss outside off, Williamson puts bat on ball and gets it through covers for two.
Flighted delivery on middle, Taylor defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Taylor defends it to short leg.
Floated delivery on middle, Taylor flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Loopy delivery on middle, Williamson flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Ross defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Taylor keeps it out.
Outside off, not played at.
One more delivery outside off, Williamson lets it be.
Good delivery! Gets it to land closer to the off pole, it angles away. Williamson hops and looks to fend at it but gets beaten.
Good length and on off, blocked.
One more short one around off, Williamson sways out of the way.
Shorter and on off, KW guides it to point.
Flighted delivery on middle, Taylor defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Taylor nudges it to short fine leg.
Full delivery on off, Taylor drives it towards mid off for a run.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Williamson nudges it to square leg.
Loopy delivery on middle, the skipper defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely played! Flighted delivery on off, Williamson guides it past first slip towards third man for a boundary.
On the pads, Taylor looks to leave it but gets hit around the hip area.
On middle, it is angling away. Taylor looks to defend but it goes off the outer half through covers for one.
Beats the outside edge! Not a lot you can do about that delivery. It lands on off which means KW has to play at it. He looks to defend but it slants away and beats the outside edge.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is a stunner from Smith at second slip. WOW! A blinder. Probably the catch of the summer for Australia. The shot though can be questioned here. Why did Williamson play that? It is a short ball outside off, Williamson looks to guide it down to third man but does not commit to the shot completely. It goes off the outside edge and flies between third slip and second slip. Smith dives horizontally, stretches his right hand out and the ball stays in. A one-handed blinder to get rid of the Kiwi skipper. A special catch to remove a special player. Also, something outstanding to break a stand which looked at ease. Williamson walks back disappointed. Maybe a lapse of concentration for him there. Played at a ball he could have left. Australia back on top now. Kiwis trail by 339 runs.
Good length and on middle, blocked.
The batsman works it down the leg side.
Flighted delivery on middle, Taylor pushes it to mid on off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Taylor defends it out.
Floated delivery on off, Taylor plays it towards point. The batsmen take a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Nicholls defends it to short leg.
Tossed up delivery outside off, Nicholls sweeps it towards fine leg. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Floated delivery on off, Nicholls blocks it off the front foot.
Shorter in length and on off, Taylor keeps it onto the ground.
Full and on off, Taylor strokes it through mid off and the batters take two.
On middle, this is worked wide of mid on for one.
Some chin music for the batter! Nicholls evades it nicely.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
Outside off, left alone.
A short one on the body, it hurries onto the batter quickly. Taylor looks to flick but it hits the higher part of the bat and goes towards fine leg for one.

NOT OUT! Once again Taylor is well in. The dive saves him there. It is shorter and on the body, Nicholls works it towards mid-wicket and takes off. Burns picks the ball up and scores a bull's eye at the striker's end. They appeal but the umpire initially shakes his head but then takes it upstairs. Replays roll in and they show Taylor is fine.
Played to the point region by the batsman. Two runs added to the total.
Shorter and on the body, RT nudges it on the leg side.

Cuts him into half! Double bluff by Cummins. The field was all set for a short one with a leg gully and a short leg in place. It is landed on a length and outside off. Jags back in. Taylor is rooted to his crease and looks to put bat to ball but his inside edge is beaten.
A single to end as this is pushed towards cover.
Bowls it down the leg side, Taylor looks to flick but misses it.

Fifty for Taylor! His 33rd in this format. Another fighting knock by the Kiwi veteran. He was peppered by the short ones, he looked uncomfortable but is still battling it out there. Half the job is done but still another half left. He gets there by working this short ball on the leg side and gets to the other end.
On off, blocked.
This is on the pads, Nicholls looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
A bumper now, Nicholls spots it early and moves out of the way.

Some excitement around the bat but Paine does not review it. It is another length ball outside off, Nicholls looks to push at it but is beaten. Labuschagne at short leg is very interested. Starc though is seen walking back straightaway. No review in the end. Snicko shows nothing. Quite funny that from Marnus, he is the only one screaming in appeal and even said that he 100 percent heard the faintest nick.
This is angled into the pads, the batter looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Back of a length again, Taylor stands back and defends it out nicely.
On a good length and around off, blocked.
Shorter and on off, Taylor drags it towards leg gully.
Short delivery on middle, Taylor nudges it past short leg for a single.
Outside off, Nicholls offers no shot to this one.
Shorter in length and outside off, Taylor rides on top of the bounce and pushes it through covers. Easy three.
Back of a length and on off, HN defends it.
Two! Down the leg side, Nicholls works it wide of fine leg and takes two.
Another two! Good effort in the field. This is on the pads, Nicholls works it wide of the fielder at fine leg. He runs to his right, slides and saves two for his side.

OUT! Nicholls is strangled down the leg side. Third time lucky for Starc. His third. The left-arm seamer is stepping up when his team needs him to do so. This though is a lucky wicket. The last two deliveries were similar, they were worked towards fine leg for two. This time though, it is another delivery down the leg side. Nicholls looks to flick but the ball kisses the edge and goes to Paine who takes it, appeals and up goes the finger. Henry is disgusted with himself as he walks back. New Zealand in deep trouble now. Can Australia get another before Stumps?

OUT! TIMBER! They have taken another on the next ball itself and Starc is on a hat-trick. The nightwatchman lasts just the one ball. Half the side back in the hut for New Zealand even before they cross 100. It is a very full delivery outside off from Starc. Wagner is in two minds there and eventually looks to jam it out but does so away from his body. It hits the inside edge and crashes into the stumps. The crowd is going mad. Starc is on fire! Australia finishing the day brilliantly.
Fuller and on middle, Taylor works it through mid-wicket and a single is taken.
Outside off, left alone.
One more delivery left alone as it is outside off.
On middle, Watling gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
A length delivery to end! BJ is solid in defense.
Fuller and wide outside off, Watling does not fiddle with it.
Nope! It is a short one just outside off, Taylor looks to cut but it is too close to play that shot. He ends up chopping it on the off side.
100 up for Kiwis! Shorter and on off, Taylor pushes it through covers and takes two.
One more short one on middle, it is pulled through square leg and a single is taken.
Outside off, it is left alone.
On the middle pole, Watling keeps it out nicely.
A little too wide outside off, not played at.
Full delivery on middle, Taylor drives it to mid on.

EDGY FOUR! Just wide of the second slip fielder! What was Taylor thinking? So late in the day, that is not even a half volley, why would you go after that delivery? Length delivery outside off, Taylor looks to slash at it but gets an outside edge. It goes uppishly wide of the second slip fielder and into the third man fence. Lucky escape for Rosco. He would have been gutted had he got out that way.
Outside off, Ross lets it go.
Bowls a bouncer, Taylor does well to duck under it.
Full delivery on off, Taylor looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

FOUR! Something to cheer for the Kiwis as Taylor plays a fantastic on drive to finish things off. Cummins is very full in his length as he spears it on middle, Taylor presents a straight bat and drives it past mid on. Neser (sub) can only retrieve the ball from the rope and that will be STUMPS ON DAY 2!
Not a bad nut to start. An inswinger, albeit a full toss, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, pushed through the covers for a single. The Kiwis are underway for the day.
Around off, defended solidly.
A short ball, around leg stump, tucked towards short leg.

Is that out? Nope. Pad. A length ball down the leg side, Taylor looks to tuck but misses. The ball goes off something behind and Paine dives to his left to collect. Someone appeals but nothing from the bowler or keeper. Hit the thigh pad.
Down the leg side again, left alone.
Full delivery on middle, Watling flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a good length on middle, Watling looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. Probably height could have been an issue there.
Good length delivery on middle, Watling defends it off the back foot.
On a good length again on middle, Watling defends it towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, Watling shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on off, Watling defends it off the back foot.
Bowls a bouncer on leg, Taylor does well to duck under it.
Short delivery down the leg side, Taylor looks to pull but misses it. It goes safely towards the keeper.
Bowls a bouncer again outside leg, Taylor does not bother to play at it.

RUN OUT CHANCE MISSED! Oh dear, oh dear, pain for Paine and Australia. And guess who is down in more pain? Nathan Lyon. Remember Headingley a few months ago? More fondly remembered as Stokesingley? Nathan Lyon missed a series-winning run out there. But here, not too sure whether he can be blamed totally. Length delivery on off, Taylor taps it towards covers. He takes the single and Watling returns for the second. However, Taylor takes a few steps and then says no. Watling has no option but to go back. Nathan Lyon gets to the ball from backward point, picks the ball and throws it at the keeper's end. BJ is gone for all money but Tim Paine fails to collect the ball and misses a massive chance of a run out there. The reason for the miss of Paine was that in the corner of his left eye, he saw Marnus Labuschagne get to collect the ball from short leg. Hence, he just took his eyes off the ball at the last moment. And hence, the ball bounces hard into his gloves and drops down. Watling comes back in. Costly. Really costly.
Full delivery on off, Watling drives it through covers. The batsmen cross ends. This time Nathan Lyon collects the ball from point and returns a very good throw. The crowd cheers.
Bowls it down the leg side, Taylor lets it go.
On a good length on off, Watling defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Classic shot! Full delivery on middle, Watling drives it through mid on for a boundary.
Bowls a bouncer, Watling ducks under it.
On a good length and just outside off, Watling offers no shot to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Watling defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Watling defends it out.
Length delivery on leg, Taylor flicks it towards the leg side.
On a good length on middle, Taylor plays it towards mid on. The batsmen cross ends.
Full and outside off, Watling drives this through mid off and gets a couple.
Around middle, pushed towards mid on.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Got him! Caught behind! Nope. Full and outside off, Watling leans to drive but misses. There is a noise but that was of the bat hitting the ground. An appeal was made but Aleem Dar shook his head.
Down the leg side, Taylor misses his flick and is hit on the pads. A leg bye taken.
Outside off, left alone.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! Missed run out? No worries. Australia's golden boy is here, while Watling is out of here. Aussies have a real chance of bowling out the Kiwis for a low score here. Cummins dishes out a good length ball on off, Watling is in two minds whether to leave it or defend it and then decides to do the latter. The ball kisses the inside edge and goes on to hit the stumps. Now, it all depends on Taylor to help the visitors avoid the follow-on.
Bouncer to start to de Grandhomme, it is bowled around middle, Colin does well to duck under it.
Good length ball outside off, de Grandhomme pushes it to cover.
Nicely played! Full delivery outside off, Colin leans forward and creams the drive through the covers for three before the fielder can cut it off.

EDGY BUT FALLS SHORT! Back of a length delivery outside off, Taylor looks to guide it but it goes off the gloves towards second slip where Steven Smith moves to his right and fails to collect it cleanly. The batters take a single.
BOUNCER! Starc attempts a bouncer down the leg side, Taylor goes for the pull but fails to get any bat on it.
On a length on off, Taylor defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short ball on middle, Taylor camps on his back foot and hammers the pull behind square leg for a boundary. They need 89 runs to avoid the follow-on.
Short delivery outside off, Taylor attempts the pull but misses it completely.
Another short one but this one is on middle, Taylor pulls it to square leg and picks up a single.
Bowls a bouncer outside leg, Taylor ducks under it.
On a good length on middle, Taylor defends it towards short leg.
Bowls a bumper outside leg, Taylor does well to duck under it.
Bowls again a bouncer, Taylor easily ducks under it.
Short delivery on middle, Taylor pulls it through square leg for a single.
FOUR! Nice shot. Full delivery outside off, de Grandhomme drives it uppishly through mid off for a boundary.

Starts with a short ball on middle, Taylor pulls it nicely towards deep square leg and picks up a couple. Michael Neser, the substitute fielder comes across from deep mid-wicket and dives to make an excellent stop.
Floated ball outside off, Taylor pushes this to deep cover and gives Colin de Grandhomme the strike.
Floated ball outside off, de Grandhomme lets the ball go to the keeper.
Flatter delivery outside off with a little bit of air, Grandhomme cuts it  towards point and picks up a single.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.
Shorter delivery outside off, Taylor cuts it to point for nothing.
Flatter delivery on off, de Grandhomme pushes it to long on and takes a single.
What was that? That is some turn! An off spinner outside off, Taylor looks to drive that but the ball sneaks past the inside half of his bat and goes into the mitts of the keeper.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery going straight on outside off, Taylor looks to cut it but fails to make any connection to it.
Full delivery on middle, Taylor sweeps it but it hits Wade on the arm at short leg. No run.
Short ball on middle, Taylor defends it off the back foot.
Low full toss outside off, Colin pushes it to long off and picks up a single.
Flatter delivery outside off, Taylor leaves this ball alone.
BEATEN! Quicker delivery outside off, Taylor looks to cut it but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and Paine collects it safely.
Shorter delivery on middle, Taylor defends it off the back foot.
Fullish ball on off, Ross pushes it to cover.
Shorter delivery outside off, Taylor punches it to point for nothing.

Flatter delivery around off, de Grandhomme looks to defend it but it goes off the outside edge towards third man. Neser hares after it from point and cuts it off but cannot stop the batters to take a couple.
Full delivery on off, Colin drives it back to the bowler.
On middle, pushes this towards long on and takes a single.
Flatter delivery on off, Taylor guides it towards point and takes a single.
OHH! Flighted ball on middle and leg, Colin looks to flick it but gets hit on the pads. There is a stifled appeal made for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
Some spin again! Lyon bowls a floated ball on off spinning into the batsman, Colin looks to flick it but it hits the inside edge of the bat and goes onto hit the pads. No run.
Flatter delivery outside off, Taylor lets the ball go the keeper.
Fullish ball outside off, Taylor drives this to deep cover and takes a single.
Loopy ball on off, de Grandhomme pushes it to deep cover again and takes a single.
Short on off, Taylor stands tall and guides it to short third man.
On off again, Taylor lunges forward and pushes it to cover.
Fuller one outside off, Taylor drives it to the off side and will keep strike for the next over.
Flighted delivery outside off, Taylor looks to sweep but misses it. Tim Paine collects the ball and whips the bails off but Ross Taylor was never out of his crease.
BEATEN! Tossed up delivery outside off, Taylor looks to defend but misses it.
DIRECT HIT BUT SAFE! Floated delivery on off, Taylor drives it towards covers where Travis Head picks the ball and fires a direct hit at the keeper's end but Ross Taylor was well in.
Around off on a fullish length, Taylor pushes it back to the bowler.
Another one around off, Taylor blocks it out off the front foot.

OUT! Lyon strikes and the Australians get the massive wicket of Taylor. No century for him. What was going through his mind? Let us try and see this period off till Drinks? Lyon bowls it full and just around off. Now, normally, Rosco would have attempted a cover drive. But perhaps, he was consumed by the fact that there was a break round the corner. Taylor lunges forward and looks to defend it towards the off side. The ball goes straight on, takes the outside edge and goes towards Steven Smith at first slip. He bends low and pouches it comfortably, just above the turf. Also, commendable effort from Travis Head on the third ball of this over. Had that been a single, Rosco might still have been batting!
Good length ball on middle, de Grandhomme defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length ball on off, Colin guides it to gully for nothing.

FOUR! That is hit with some power! Starc bowls a short one on off, de Grandhomme rocks on his back foot and pulls it with some disdain to the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary. There is a man in the deep but it is well ahead of him. He is more at squarish mid-wicket. One bounce and into the fence.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for de Grandhomme! Back of a length delivery outside off, Colin guides this through the gully region for a boundary. He is looking in good touch here. Is he aiming to up the ante? He has got 4 half centuries in his last 5 Test innings. Not a bad time to make it 5 out of 6.
Short ball around middle, de Grandhomme lets the ball go to the keeper.

OUT! CAUGHT! What is happening here? Lot of confusion going around! The third umpire has told Aleem Dar, the onfield umpire that he has no conclusive evidence to overturn the decision. 5-fer for Starc, though it can be argued whether this was a wicket in the first place. Nasty bouncer, bowled around middle and off, de Grandhomme looks to defend it off the back foot but the ball suddenly shoots up. It goes off something to Steven Smith at second slip who pouches it safely to his left. Now, Starc straightaway celebrates and so do the Aussies. However, de Grandhomme looks a bit confused. He asks Aleem Dar who now gives it out. Colin looks bemused and consults his partner for a review. Signals the 'T'. Here come the replays. Now, by the first look, to the naked eye, from the side on angle, it seems like it has kissed the helmet. But has it kissed the glove or the outside edge? Now, Hot Spot shows nothing on the gloves and then the Ultra Edge rolls in. There is a spike. But, AFTER it goes past the gloves. The third umpire takes multiple looks at it and with every look, it seems like it has missed the glove. However, Marais Erasmus does not want to take any risks and tells Dar that he is not sure whether there is any conclusive evidence to overturn the decision. So, the decision stays as it is. Tough, tough luck for Colin. He will feel robbed. And the Kiwis are robbed of a review as well. If the third umpire is not sure, shouldn't the benefit of doubt go to the batsman? Possible thoughts about changing the rule?
Fires it on middle, Santner looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes towards square leg for a single.
Around off, it is defended.
Slightly shortish length and around off, Southee goes back and keeps it out.
On off this time, Southee gets behind the line of the ball and defends it out.
Flighted around off and middle, Southee once again lunges and pushes it towards cover.
Full and just outside off, it is defended nicely.
Fullish length ball on middle, Santner tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Bouncer and a well directed one too. Southee looks to duck initially then looks to pull but gets hit on the arm guard. The ball goes towards Paine on the bounce.
Another back of a length ball down the leg side, Southee looks to pull again but misses out.
On the leg stump line again, this is just behind shortish length, Southee looks to tuck it towards fine leg but misses out to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards fine leg for a leg bye.
Beaten! A good length ball outside off, Santner looks to drive but the ball shapes away a hint and goes past the bat to Paine.
Beaten again! Another shortish length ball, this is angled in too. Santner has a poke again but once again it goes past the outside edge. Another excellent over from Starc.
Flatter delivery on off, Southee punches this off the back foot to the bowler.
Full delivery on off, Tim lunges forward and drives it to mid off.

EDGY FOUR! Lucky boundary for Southee. Lyon bowls a flatter delivery outside off, Southee stands tall to cut it but it hits the bottom edge of the bat and goes towards the third man region for a boundary. Gets off the mark with that does Southee. The fielder from the slip cordon runs after it but fails to reach it on time.
On off, defended off the back foot by Southee.
Flatter delivery outside off, Southee lets the ball go the keeper.
Short ball outside off, Tim punches the ball off the back foot to the off side.
Good length ball around off, it is defended off the back foot towards cover.
Shortish and just around off, Santner stays on the back foot and taps it towards point.
On middle this one, it is pushed back to the bowler.
Bouncer and around off, Santner ducks under it.
Fuller one on off, Santner comes forward and defends it out.
Yorker now! A good one too but Santner is up for the challenge as he digs it out nicely.
Flatter one around off, Southee pushes it back to the bowler.
Fires it full and outside off, Southee reaches out and pushes it towards cover.
Flatter one on off, it is defended.

Edge again, but wide of first slip. Excellent from the sub Michael Neser though who dives and pulls the ball back in play, just before the ropes. Lyon gives it a lot of air and bowls it wide of off. Southee looks to block but gets an outside edge which goes wide of the diving Smith. It races towards the fence but Neser gives it a chase and makes an excellent stop to save a single. Three for Southee.
Around middle, Santner keeps it out.
Shortish one, Santner stays back and pushes it towards mid off.
Around off, pushed towards point.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Bowls it full and just outside off, driven through covers for a single.
Fires it on the pads, Santner looks to work it around the corner but misses to get hit on the pads.

Full and on off, Santner drives it back to the bowler nicely. However, Labuschagne gets down to field. It is too straight and hence it goes to hit the stumps. A stifled appeal from Marnus. Aleem Dar goes upstairs. The replays roll in, and it is not sure if Marnus got his hands to the ball. However, Southee is in his crease so not out it is.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Beaten! It is outside off and a flatter one, Southee goes to cut but misses.
Flighted ball outside off, Southee comes forward to defend but misses out to get hit on the thigh pad.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Looks to sweep this time but misses. It is outside off though but Southee goes for the sweep but misses out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Shortish length ball around off, Southee goes back and keeps it out.
Around off, defended from the crease.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.

OUT! BOWLED! Off the rough! Aha... Marnus Warne has a wicket. Nope, that is not a mistake in the name. That is genuinely a good ball. Full and outside off, Santner looks to drive. But this one has landed on the rough. It then spins back in, goes past the inside edge and hits the timber. Marnus is running along, almost doing an Imran Tahir.
Beaten! Nice turn and bounce! It pitches around middle and off and then turns away from the defensive prod of Ferguson.
Wide outside off, it is left alone. End of an excellent over from Labuschagne.
Flatter one and outside off, Southee keeps it out.

OUT! Caught! That's it. New Zealand are all out. Lyon flights it outside off, inviting Southee for the slog. He obliges and  launches it out of the park. He, however, only manages to slice it up high towards point. Neser settles under it and pouches it easily. Southee was defending till the time he had Santner for company but now with an injured Ferguson at the other end, Southee had no other choice than trying to score quickly. He tries and perishes in that attempt. NEW ZEALAND ARE ALL OUT FOR 166.
Beaten first up! Full and outside off, Warner is lured into the shot as he drives away from the body. Quite a risky shot this one at this moment of time. 5 more balls to survive before lunch.
Good length ball around off, it is defended.
Warner is underway! Another good length ball, this is on the pads, Warner tucks it towards fine leg for a single. 3 tricky balls for Burns then.
In the channel outside off first up for the right-hander. Unlike Warner, Burns is not lured as he shoulders arms.
Another one outside off on a good length, Burns lets it be. Last ball before Lunch coming up.
Full and on middle, Burns pushes it towards mid on to see off the over. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3.
NO BALL! De Grandhomme oversteps on the first ball of his spell. Full ball on the pads, Warner tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Shortish ball outside off, pushed towards short third man with an angled bat.
Around off, it is defended.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length ball around off, Burns keeps it out.
In the channel outside off, Burns shoulders arms.
Another one in the corridor of uncertainty. Burns is not attacking these as he lets it go to the keeper. Colin needs to get closer to the timbers here.
Southee starts with a good length ball outside off, Warner has his stumps covered as he shoulders arms.
Fuller and just outside off, Warner drives it well but straight to mid off. Burns was probably interested for a single but Warner shouts a loud no.
Fuller and around off, it is defended off the front foot towards cover.

FOUR! Lovely timing! First boundary of the innings. Goes full just around off, Warner leans forward and drives it through mid off for a boundary. The mid off fielder gives it a chase but the ball wins the race.
Good length ball around off, Warner keeps it out.
In the channel outside off, Warner lets it be.
Shortish length ball around off, Burns taps it off the back foot onto the pitch.
Fuller one and on off, driven firmly but straight to the cover fielder.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Second leave in a row as de Grandhomme bowls it outside off on a good length.
Fuller one, pushed towards cover.

Nearly a drag on! Shortish length ball around off, Burns stays on the back foot and looks to block. He though manages an inside edge which drops near the stumps and then bounces over it. Burns survives a scare.
On the pads, Warner looks to tickle it around the corner to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards fine leg and a leg bye is taken.
Outside off on a good length, it shapes away as it goes past Burns who allows it to go to the keeper.
Fullish and driveable ball outside off. Burns is not falling for the trap as he lets it be. Two slips are waiting for the outside edge.
Around off, Burns comes forward and keeps it out off the front foot.
Good length ball angled into the right-hander. Burns punches it towards mid  on.
Shortish length ball, just outside off, Burns taps it towards gully. 20 balls and Burns is yet to get off the mark.
Beaten! Shortish length, not too wide off the off pole. Warner goes on the back foot to cut but makes no connection.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length ball around off, Warner taps it towards the off side and shouts a loud no to his partner.
Around off, this time Warner pushes it towards point and takes a quick run.
Good length ball around off, Burns pushes it towards mid off.
Outside off, it is left alone by Burns.
Fuller and outside off, Warner thinks to go for the drive but then curbs his instinct at the last moment.
Around off on a length, pushed towards cover.
In the channel outside off again but it is on a length. Warner shoulders arms.
FOUR! Full and outside off, Warner drives it through point nicely. The ball races to the fence. The boundary brings 7000 Test runs for Warner, 12th Australian to do so.
Good length ball just outside off, Warner defends it out.

Beauty to end the over! Length ball outside off, Warner thinks this will come in with the angle. However, Southee takes it the other way by rolling his fingers on the ball. Warner pokes and is beaten.
On off, Burns keeps it out.
Landed on middle, Burns turns it towards square leg.

Finally, Burns is off the mark! Full and just outside off, Burns drives it through covers. Santner from point chases the ball down and keeps it to two. Brilliant effort from him. Burns though will be a relieved man now.
Length ball around off, Burns pushes it towards point.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and on off, Burns drives it nicely but straight to mid off.
Shortish length ball, closer to off. Warner covers his stumps and lets it be.
Around off on a good length, Warner defends it out.
Good length ball outside off, Warner lets it be.
Beaten! This one kept low! A cross seamed ball just outside off, it pitches and then comes in as Warner looks to defend. Watling pouches it low in front of him. That cut him into half.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

Brute of a yorker from Southee. Warner looks to flick but misses out. A loud appeal from Southee and the players from slip cordon but umpire is not interested. Looked like a big inside edge on that one. No review taken from the Kiwis.
On the pads, Burns guides it towards fine leg for a single.
Shortish and outside off, Warner first lets it be and when the ball goes past him, he tries to upper cut it but makes no connection.
Another shortish length ball outside off, Warner this time is clear that he is going to let it go to the keeper.
Outside off, it is left alone.
FOUR! Tickled nicely! Not a good ball this one. It is on the pads of Warner. All he needs to do is get a tickle, he does it nicely and it goes to the fence.

NOT OUT! Warner stays, New Zealand lose a review. Brilliant bowling from de Grandhomme. He dishes out a shortish length ball just around off and middle. Warner has to play at it. He hops and looks to defend but misses out. The ball hits something and goes towards second slip. The fielder there pouches it nicely. Kiwis are confident in their appeal. It seems like Warner is going off but maybe he was going towards square leg to switch off. Williamson though goes for the review. Let's find out. First up, it is Hot Spot. Nothing conclusive from it. Not the proper angle to view it. Here comes Snicko. No deflection as it goes past the gloves. Then as the ball passes the gloves, it hits the shoulder and there's the deflection of the same on the Snicko. Don't change your decision says Erasmus to Aleem Dar. Warner to continue, the Kiwis go one review down.

FOUR! A loosener to start off from Wagner! A half volley outside off, Burns leans into his drive and drives it past the diving fielder at cover and into the fence. The fielder from mid off chases after it but fails to keep it inside the fence.
On a length on middle, Joe defends it out off the back foot.
Good length ball outside off, Burns lets the ball go to the keeper.
Fullish delivery outside off, Joe pushes it to covers for nothing.
Fuller one outside the off stump line, Burns does not fiddle with it and lets the ball go to the keeper.
This time goes full on middle does Wagner, Burns is solid in defense.
Full delivery on off, Warner punches this to mid off and shouts a loud no to Burns.
Good length ball on middle, Warner solidly blocks it out to mid on.
Fullish ball outside the off stump line, David lets the ball go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Back of a length delivery outside off, Warner attempts the pull shot but misses to get any bat on it.
Back of a length ball on off, Warner pushes it towards the cover region and picks up a single.
On a length outside off, Burns leaves it alone to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, David defends it off the front foot to mid off.
Full delivery on middle, Warner pushes it to mid on.
On a length on middle and leg, Warner works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball around off, David pushes it to cover.
Fullish delivery on middle, Warner tucks it to deep square leg and takes a single.
On middle, defended back to the bowler by Burns.
OHH! Good length ball outside off, Warner looks to cut it but it goes off the bottom edge towards the slip cordon. No harm done though.
Good length delivery on off, blocked to cover.
Good length ball outside off, David lets the ball through to the keeper.
Outside off, Warner makes another leave.
Fullish ball on off, Warner is solid in defense and does so towards cover.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Warner pushes it to mid on. Third maiden over for Southee.
Wagner bowls a full delivery on middle, Burns works it towards square leg and picks up a couple before Raval can chase it down from square leg.
On a length on off, Burns defends it to cover.

RUN OUT CHANCE MISSED! Poor judgement in running from the batsmen but Warner survives. He was nowhere in the picture. Burns defends this good length ball towards point and calls Warner for a single. Santner comes across, slides and collects it. He then has a shy at the keeper's end but misses it. Had he hit, Warner was a goner. Can Warner make NZ pay for it?
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around off, Warner lets it go to the keeper.
NO BALL! It is bowled way over, Warner is not worried and he lets the ball go to the keeper. The umpire signals it a no ball as the bowler has overstepped.
Another short one outside off, Warner looks to play the upper cut but misses it.
Full delivery outside off, Burns lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on middle, Joe defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Beautiful shot! Southee bowls a full delivery outside off, Burns lunges forward and drives it through the point region for a boundary. The fielder chases after it from point but fails to get there.
Good length ball on off, Burns looks to defend it but it goes off the inside edge to the leg side.
OHH! Very full delivery on the pads, Burns looks to flick it but misses to get hit on the pads. There is a stifled appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
FOUR! Another boundary for Burns in this over! Joe after a slow start is starting to look good now. Good length ball outside off, Burns drives this through the gully region for a boundary.
Bowls a back of a length ball, but it is sprayed way down the leg side. Warner lets it be.
Shortish length ball on middle, Warner tucks it behind square leg and gets a run.
WIDE! Fullish and wide outside off, actually way outside off. Burns lets it be but Llong stretches his arms to signal it a wide.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and just outside off, Burns pushes it towards cover. That came from the toe end of the bat.
No Ball! Wagner oversteps again. He goes short and on middle again, Burns pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
Another back of a length ball but down the leg side. Warner ducks under it.

Another no ball! Second off the over. To trouble Warner with the short stuff, Wagner is putting a little too much effort and hence probably he is crossing the line there. Another bumper on middle and leg. Warner this time goes for the pull but does not connect. Wagner while returning to his mark, has a word with the umpire there, probably asking where he is landing.
Shortish ball around off, Warner taps it towards point for a single.
Full delivery on off, Warner shouts wait on as he defends this out to the off side.
Outside off, left alone by Warner.

OHH! Impact was outside off! The impact might have just saved Warner there. Good length ball around off, Warner looks to defend it but misses it to get hit on the back pad. Southee puts in a huge appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Southee is seen talking to his skipper but it seems that Kane Williamson is not hearing it properly. In the end, they decide not to go for the review. The replays roll in and Ball Tracker shows that the impact was outside off. Good decision to not go for the review.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

That goes off the cracks! But to the bowler. Full delivery on middle, Warner drives it straight back to the bowler. Southee attempts to collect it but it hits the crack and bounces extremely low, beneath his hands! Tim looks at Warner and then smiles.

OUT! CAUGHT! Warner does not survive long after the LBW shout! After getting a start here as well, Warner gets out. Short of a length delivery on middle which hurried onto him, Warner looks to pull it but ends up top edging it. He then checks whether he won't get hit-wicket as he lost control of his willow. David then, as he goes to pick up his bat sees Blundell taking the catch at mid on and then walks off. Blundell, the substitute fielder, comes a few steps ahead and pouches it safely.
FOUR! Brilliantly timed! Overpitched and outside off. Burns leans into the shot and drives it through cover-point. It races to the fence.
Shortish ball around middle, Joe hops in the crease and keeps it out.
Variable bounce starting to come in play. Wagner tries bowling another bouncer outside off. It does not take off though and dies down as it goes to the keeper.
Shortish on off again, Burns this time rides the bounce and defends it towards cover.
Another shortish length, pushed towards gully with an angled bat.

Another one which did not get up at all. Another bouncer attempt from Wagner. This is just outside off. Burns is not sure if he should leave it or play at it. He eventually lets it be. Watling collects the ball on the bounce.
Labuschagne is underway straightaway! A nice drive too. A fuller ball just outside off, Marnus drives it towards mid off and takes off for a quick single.
AUSTRALIA'S LEAD NOW READS 300! A shortish length ball on middle, Burns rolls his wrists and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Brilliant running between the wickets! A good length ball on the pads, Labuschagne flicks it towards deep mid-wicket and runs three before the fielder can return the ball to the keeper.
Full and outside off, Burns drives it towards cover where de Grandhomme fumbles but it does not cost them a run.
Overpitched and outside off, Burns drives it nicely but straight to the mid off fielder.
Full and outside off again, another nice looking drive straight to mid off again.

Dropped! De Grandhomme puts down Labuschagne! He made all the ground by running to his right but cannot hold on. A well directed bouncer on middle, Labuschagne goes for the pull but there is extra bounce on that one and the ball comes slowly as well. As a result, he top edges it towards mid-wicket. Colin runs back from short mid-wicket, gets to the ball, puts in a dive but spills it in the end. How costly will it be? A single taken.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Short for Burns too. He pulls it towards deep square leg and takes a single.
Another short of a length ball, Labuschagne pushes it towards point.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Make that two leaves in a row. In the channel outside off, Marnus lets it be.
Starts with a tossed up ball outside off, Burns drives it to deep cover and picks up a single.
Some spin immediately. Flatter delivery outside off going away from the batsman, Labuschagne looks to defend it but it goes past the outside edge of the bat.
Flighted ball on middle, Marnus comes down the track and flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
OHH! That was close! Quicker delivery on middle which almost brushes the pad of Burns. He, luckily gets his bat down in time and guides it to point.
Flatter delivery on middle, Burns defends it off the back foot.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
FOUR! Shot! Labuschagne is continuing his form in this innings as well! Back of a length delivery outside off, Marnus rocks on his back foot and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Short ball on middle, Marnus pulls it to mid-wicket.
On a length on off, ML rocks on his back foot and blocks it to cover.
Short ball outside off, Labuschagne lets the ball go to the keeper.
Another short one on middle, Marnus defends it back to Wagner.
Flatter delivery on middle, Burns blocks it out onto the pitch.
Floated ball down the leg side, Joe looks to flick it but misses it.
FOUR! Beautiful shot and some lovely footwork! Santner bowls a flighted ball on middle, Burns takes a few quick steps ahead and hammers it straight down the ground. One bounce and into the fence.
Flatter delivery on the pads, Joe looks to work it down the leg side but gets hit on the pads.

Well fielded! Floated ball on off, Joe dances down the track but does not get to the pitch of it at all this time. He still plays the drive straight down the ground but Santner is quick to bend on his knees and collect it. Mitchell then looks to throw it back at Burns but does not do so. Burns has a wry smile on his face.
On a length on off, pushed towards point.
Fullish length ball just outside off. Labuschagne lets it be.
Shortish length ball, closer to off pole again. Labuschagne has his stumps covered as he allows the ball go to the keeper.
Another short ball outside off, Labuschagne cuts it through gully and picks a couple.

Edged but does not carry to Taylor at first slip. Full ball around off, this time Labuschagne is drawn into the shot as he drives. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards Taylor at first slip but it goes on the bounce. He does well to field it.
Around off, Labuschagne keeps it out off the front foot.
Shortish ball around off, Labuschagne taps it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on the pads, Burns attempts to work it on the leg side but gets hit on the pads.
Floated delivery on the pads, Burns sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Delicate touch! Flatter delivery outside off, Labuschagne waits for it and then guides it through gully for a couple. Wagner, the man with a lot of stamina, hares after it and cleans it up.
Full delivery on middle, Marnus flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter delivery outside off, ML punches it to deep cover and picks up a couple.
On middle, flicked to deep square leg and picks up a single.
Full delivery on off, Marnus drives it to mid off for nothing.

NOT OUT! Waste of a review! Watling was confident in his appeal. Good length ball tailing in, Labuschagne fails to read it and decides to leave it. It hits the pocket of the trouser and goes to the keeper. Watling appeals after collecting it but the umpire says no. After some thought, the Kiwis go for the review. They have lost one already. There was a distance between bat and pad so there was no chance of there being bat on it. The Ball Tracker then rolls in and it confirms that Marnus was hit on the pocket outside off. The impact won't matter as Marnus left the ball alone but the ball was going on to miss the stumps by a mile. Poor review from Kiwis and they have lost their second review as well.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Labuschagne looks to drive it but fails to get any bat on it.
Full on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Dropped short! Short delivery on middle, Burns pulls it uppishly but it goes on the bounce to the square leg fielder.
Around off, solidly defended. TEA ON DAY 2, AUS LEAD BY 325!
Santner starts with a fullish ball around off, Burns comes forward to defend but the ball takes the inner half of the bat and goes towards square leg for a single.
Gives this one a lot of air and lands it around off again. Labuschagne blocks it out nicely.
Slightly quicker and on middle, Labuschagne turns it with the spin towards square leg for a run.
Another ball on middle, Burns this time works it towards square leg and crosses for a run.
Around off, it is defended.
Nicely bowled! Fires this one on the stumps line, Labuschagne gets his bat down in time to keep it out.
Good length ball on middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and outside off, Burns leans and pushes it towards cover for a single.
Good length ball just outside off, Marnus lets it be.
Landed around off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
Fuller and around off, Labuschagne drives well but straight to the cover fielder.
Full and on off again, ML this time drives it to mid on.
Full delivery on off, Burns drives it to covers.
Floated delivery on off, Burns plays it towards covers for a run.
Tossed up delivery on off, Labuschagne comes down the track and plays it back towards the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Marnus flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Loopy delivery on off, Marnus punches it towards point for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Burns keeps it out.
Full on off, driven firmly by Labuschagne but straight to the cover fielder again.
WIDE! This time Grandhomme bends his back and bowls a bouncer but it is way over the head of the batsman there. Wided by the umpire.
On the pads this time, Marnus looks to work it fine down the leg side but gets hit high on the pads. The ball rolls towards square leg and the batters cross for a leg bye.
Outside off, it is left alone.
No Ball! De Grandhomme oversteps now. Fuller ball around off, Burns looks to flick but gets a leading edge which goes towards cover for a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

Shortish length ball outside off, Labuschagne waits for the ball and then guides it through gully and second slip. The ball races to the fence but Taylor gives it a chase and makes a sliding stop to save a run.
Fullish and outside off, Burns keeps it out.

FOUR! 50-run stand is up! Brilliant use of the feet from Marnus. Santner flights this outside off, Labuschagne skips down the track and slams it over the cover region and into the fence. Brilliant stand this one. Also, the boundary brings up 1000 Test runs for Labuschagne in 2019.
On middle, turned towards mid-wicket for a run.
Full and around off, Burns comes forward and keeps it out.
FOUR! Second one off the over. Santner bowls it short and wide. This time Burns waits on the back foot and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Shortish and on off, Burns goes back and then comes forward to turn it behind square for a single. 100 comes up for the Aussies. The lead touches 350 too.
Flatter around off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
On a length on middle, Burns flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length delivery on off, Burns plays it to point.
Good length delivery on off, Burns defends it out.
On a good length on middle, Joe defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, Burns offers no shot to this one.
Good length delivery on middle, Burns keeps it out.
On a good length on off, Labuschagne defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on off, Labuschagne defends it out.

FOUR! Why is there no third man in place? If there was a fielder placed it would have gone straight into his hands. Short and outside off, Labuschagne plays an upper cut over third man for a boundary.
Length delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Short and outside off, Burns cuts it through point. The batsmen get two runs.
Full delivery outside off, Burns drives it through covers. Two runs taken.
On a length on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on middle, Labuschagne defends it out.
On a length on middle, Marnus flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Outside off, Marnus shoulders arms to this one.
Again outside off, Labuschagne lets it go.
Good length ball just outside off, Burns guides it towards third man and gets three closer to his half ton.
Nicely bowled! Bouncer on middle, Labuschagne does well to sway away from it.

Good length ball just outside off, Labuschagne tucks it towards the leg side. Burns wants a single. Labuschagne is not interested. Southee gets to the ball and aim the stumps at the non-striker's end. Burns dives to make his crease. However, Southee misses his shy at the stumps. There is a collision between umpire Aleem Dar and Santner. Mitchell was probably coming to collect the throw while Dar was trying to stay away from the firing line. Aleem Dar is down.
Short of a length delivery, Labuschagne pulls it over mid-wicket. The batsmen take a single.
Length delivery outside off, Burns guides it towards point for a run.
Outside off, Marnus offers no shot to this one.
BEATEN! Beautiful bowling! Full delivery outside off with extra bounce, Burns pushes at it from inside the crease but misses it completely. Watling collects it near his head.
Outside off, Burns pushes it to point.
Good length ball on off, Burns looks to defend it but it goes off the inside edge past the stumps.  A single taken.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Short ball on middle, Labuschagne pulls it to fine leg and takes a single.
Full delivery on off, pushed to point.
Brilliant running between the wickets! On a length on middle, Labuschagne flicks it through mid-wicket. He calls for two and Burns responds quickly.
Short ball on middle, Marnus pulls it towards deep square leg for a single now.
6th Test half ton for Joe Burns. A very well composed one from him. A full ball around off, Burns pushes it through covers and takes a single to reach the landmark.
Outside off, left alone.
Around off this one, tucked towards the leg side and a quick run taken.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Back of a length ball on middle, Marnus pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
Short and outside off, Burns looks to pull but gets a bottom edge which goes to the left of the keeper who dives to stop it well.
Another bouncer! Burns ducks under it.
Another back of a length ball outside off, Burns lets it be again.
Fuller and just around off, tapped towards point.
Wagner looks to bowl another short ball but this one does not rise enough. Burns does well to keep it out.
Santner flights it and bowls it around off, ML pushes it back to Santner.
On the pads, worked towards short fine leg.
Another ball on the pads, Labuschagne flicks it but straight to fine leg.
Full and on middle, this time Labuschagne sweeps it past the diving short fine leg fielder for a couple of runs.
Flatter one around off this one, pushed towards mid on.
Fuller and around off, turned towards right of mid-wicket for a single. 3 away from another half ton.
WIDE! Another extra, third wide from Wagner. He goes short again but way over the head of the batter. Called wide.
Short again, pushed towards mid on for a single.
Short on middle, pulled towards mid-wicket.
Another ball which does not bounce! It pitches on shortish length but does not rise. Burns does well to defend it out.
WIDE! Another one for height. Wagner bends his back and bowls short. This one shoots way over the head of Burns. The umpire stretches arms once again.
Full and on the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Full and around off and middle this time, Burns pushes it towards the leg side.
Just behind good length and outside off, pushed towards gully with an angled bat.
Flighted delivery on middle, Burns drives it to long on for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Burns defends it out.
Full delivery on middle, Burns drives it through mid on. The batsmen take a single.

NOT OUT! Labuschagne is well in! Floated delivery on middle, Marnus flicks it towards mid-wicket. Marnus wants the run but Burns sends him back. The fielder fires a direct hit at the keeper's end. It is referred upstairs. The replays show that Labuschagne was well inside the crease.
Shortish and on middle, pushed towards mid on.
FIFTY FOR LABUSCHAGNE. His 6th in Tests. What a fabulous year he is having. A full ball outside off, Labuschagne drives it through covers and takes a single.
Bouncer and around off, Marnus blocks it back to the bowler.

OUT! Caught! Wagner strikes. Gets him second time in a row. He has persisted with the short stuff and finally it pays the dividend for him. Another bouncer on middle, Labuschagne takes the challenge and goes for the pull but he cannot time it to his liking. It lobs towards Santner at mid-wicket who takes it easily. A  fine innings from him comes to end.
Good length ball around off, Smith defends it out coming forward.
Down the leg side. Smith comes across the off pole and allows the ball go through to the keeper.
On middle, Smith turns it behind square leg for a single to get off the mark.
Bumper but outside off, Burns lets it be.
Full and on middle, Smith pushes it towards mid on off the front foot.
Outside off, Smith lets it be.
Another ball outside off, Smith makes another leave.
Good length ball around off, tapped towards point.

FOUR! Driven handsomely! Full and outside off, Smith gets to the pitch and slams it to the left of the short cover fielder. The ball races to the fence in a jiffy. Nowhere near the line of the delivery but superb hand-eye coordination fetches him these runs.
FOUR! Wow! From the middle of the bat. Full and on off, Smith drills it past the bowler and into the fence. Brilliantly timed this one.
Good length ball around off, Burns pushes it back to the bowler who gets to his right and fields.
Short of a length ball on middle, pulled behind square for a single.
Bouncer on middle, Smith ducks under it.
Another short of a length ball but down the leg side. Smith lets it go to the keeper.
Full and on off, Smith flicks it towards mid-wicket where Santner misfields and allows a single.
Shortish and outside off, cut towards gully where the fielder does well to move to his right and field.
On middle, turned towards square leg.
Bowls a bouncer outside leg, Smith sways away from it.
WIDE! Bowls a bumper again, Smith ducks under it. The umpire gives it wide for height.

Huge appeal for LBW but not out says the umpire. No reviews left for the Kiwis. Anyway, that looked to be pitching outside leg. It pitched around leg and kept low. Smith looks to flick but mises to get hit on the pads. Southee and the Kiwis appeal but nothing doing.
Now this one shoots off! Good length delivery on off, Smith looks to defend but the ball rises on him. He somehow manages to keep it down off his gloves.
FOUR! That is put away! Short delivery on leg, Smith pulls it through square leg. The fielder tries to stop it but it goes through him into the fence.
Length delivery on middle, Steven nudges it towards square leg.
Back of a length ball around off, Burns pulls it towards mid-wicket.
Another shortish length ball outside off, Burns cuts it through point for a single.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length ball, Smith blocks it towards the leg side.
Short again, this time Smith goes for the pull but misses out to time it well.
Length delivery down the leg side, Burns looks to flick but misses it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Burns is a goner and Australia lose their third wicket. Southee bowls a well-directed bouncer, on middle and off. Burns looks to hop and get over the ball in an attempt to keep it down. He only manages to get his glove on it. The ball flies towards the gully region where Henry Nicholls takes an easy catch. Southee gets his 2nd wicket of the innings and Australia are now 398/3 effectively.
Bouncer straight up to Wade! He does well to evade it.
Wade goes back in his crease and defends this length ball off the back foot.
Bouncer again to Wade, he ducks under it this time.
Length ball outside off, Wade opts to leave this one.
Length delivery on off, Smith taps it to point.
Short of a length delivery on middle, Smith looks to defend but gets hit on the glove.
Short again on leg, Smith pulls it to short fine leg.
Short delivery on middle, Smith pulls it through mid-wicket for a run.
Bowls a bouncer, Wade easily ducks under it.
On a good length on off, Wade defends it off the back foot.
