Short delivery on leg, Smith pulls it through mid-wicket for a single. Australia are effectively 400/3.
On a good length on off, Wade defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Wade keeps it out.

FOUR! Southee tries the short ball tactic with Wade at the other end. Wade is up for the challenge as he pulls it through square leg. There is no one manning that area as the ball crosses the ropes in a flash.
Bowls a bouncer outside leg, Wade ducks under it.
Outside off, Wade shoulders arms to this one.

OUT! CAUGHT! Steven Smith now departs and Australia lose 2 wickets in quick succession! Wagner bowls a bouncer this time, on middle and leg. Smith looks to pull this powerfully but does not get the perfect timing on it. The ball goes a bit uppishly to the right of Jeet Raval at square leg who tumbles to that side and takes the catch. Smith looks really disappointed as he goes back to the pavilion. Australia have to be careful here not to lose wickets in a heap.
Down the leg side, Head looks to flick it fine down the leg side but misses.
On the pads again, Head flicks it towards the square leg region and takes a single to get off the mark.

Appeal but nothing doing! Another bouncer, on middle and off. Wade looks to fend at it but fails to do so and the ball flies towards keeper BJ Watling. He takes the catch and appeals but the umpire is unmoved. No reviews left for New Zealand. Replays roll in and show that it hit the arm guard.
This time a back of a length ball on middle and leg. Wade looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. The ball goes to the right of Watling who makes a diving stop.
Bouncer on middle and off, ducked under.
Short delivery on leg, Head nudges it towards the leg side.
Good length delivery on off, Head defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short delivery on leg angled into the ribs, Travis flicks it towards fine leg for a boundary.
On a length on middle, Head nudges it towards the leg side.
Bowls a bouncer, Head lets it sail through to the keeper.
WIDE! Bowls a bouncer outside leg, Head sways away from it. The umpire gives it wide for height.

OUT! TAKEN! Southee gets another wicket and this time it is Travis Head. Wickets falling like nine-pins for Australia right now. Southee bowls a short ball down the leg side, it stays a touch low after pitching. Head looks to help it fine down the leg side but he does so uppishly. Colin de Grandhomme at leg gully takes a simple catch and half the Australian side back in the hut now.
Length ball down the leg side, worked towards the leg side.

Bouncer on middle and off, Wade looks to defend by getting on top of it but the ball hits the gloves. Wagner stares at Wade in his followthrough and Wade gives a look back. Finally signs of some fire in the contest.
Knuckle ball by Wagner, it is a full toss on the pads. Wade flicks this one towards mid-wicket.
Wagner follows up the misdirected knuckle ball beautifully by bowling a perfect yorker on the off pole. Wade does well to dig it out.
Bouncer again, Wade evades it.
Another bouncer, Wade is not able to get his bat at it and is hit on the body.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around leg stump, Paine ducks under it.

OUT! TIMBER! Australia are collapsing under the lights at Perth. Are New Zealand in with a chance? Good length ball tailing back in, Paine looks to flick it but the ball sneaks between the bat and pad, going onto hit the middle stump. The Australian skipper looks surprised and is having a look at the pitch before making his way back to the pavilion. The Kiwis bowling with a spring in their steps now. Can they take another wicket before Stumps?
Good length ball down the leg side, Cummins looks to flick but misses it.
Short ball around middle, Cummins is ready for it and ducks under it.
Fullish ball down the leg side again, Pat looks to flick it but fails to put any bat on it.
Back of a length ball on the pads, Cummins tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full toss on off, Wade plays it to covers.
Full delivery on off, Wade drives it to covers again.
On a good length on middle, Wade blocks it off the front foot.
Bowls a bouncer, Wade lets it sail through to the keeper.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Wade sways away from it.
Bowls a bumper again, Wade ducks under it.
Short delivery on leg, Cummins flicks it just past short leg.
On a good length on middle, Cummins defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Cummins defends it off the back foot.
Bowls a yorker on middle, Cummins does well to dig it out.
WIDE! Bowls a bouncer, Cummins easily ducks under it.
On a length on middle, Cummins flicks it to mid-wicket.
On a good length on off, Cummins blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Full toss on leg, Wade flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Bowls a bouncer on leg, Wade looks to duck but gets hit on the shoulder. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen take a run. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Cummins looks to drive it but fails to get any bat on it.
Back of a length ball on middle, Cummins flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.

Just short! Wade is lucky here! Good length ball on middle and leg, Matthew looks to flick it but it goes off the inside edge onto the pads and lobs towards Latham at short leg. Tom dives to catch it but it falls short.
Full delivery on middle, Wade defends it back to the bowler. STUMPS ON DAY 3.
A bouncer to start the day, Cummins ducks.
Full and around middle, pushed towards mid on.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Another bouncer, around middle, Pat ducks.
Full and down the leg side, PC looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. The ball rolls to the leg side.
First runs of the day. Full and down the leg side, Cummins tickles it towards fine leg for a couple.
A bouncer, on middle, Wade ducks.
Another bouncer, around middle and off, Matthew ducks again.
Full and around middle and leg, tucked towards short leg.

OUCH! That has hurt. Wade is wincing in pain. A short ball, around leg stump, Matthew looks to tuck it to the leg side but the ball bounces sharply and pings him on the gloves of the bottom hand. Did that hit a crack? MW immediately takes his gloves off, walks away a touch but then makes himself ready to face. Tough man.

OUCH AGAIN! Wagner is softening Wade up. He is giving that nasty smile but Wade is smiling even nastier! Is he thinking, 'Wait till you face Starc or Cummins, mate'? A short ball, outside leg, Matthew does not know how to play that, so just offers no shot. The ball hits him on the arm guard but he shows no pain.
Down the leg side again, left alone.
A length ball, around off, coming in, Cummins looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. There is a mild LBW shout but that looked too high.
Around middle worked wide of mid on for a couple. The lead is now 421. The stand moves to 11.
A length ball around off, Pat looks to defend but the ball bounces a shade extra, takes the outside edge and lands in front of wide first slip. Actually, it is almost a second slip.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, quietly left alone.
One more leave outside off. De Grandhomme, as usual, testing the patience of the batsman.
A bouncer, down the leg side, ducked under.
Another bouncer, ducked again. How long will this duel go on? How long will Wagner keep on bowling bouncers? Till eternity. How long will Wade keep on leaving them alone? Patience-tester.

FOUR LEG BYES but dead ball signalled. A bouncer, down the leg side, Wade does not offer any shot. The ball hits his right arm and goes to the fine leg fence. The batsmen start to run but umpire Nigel Llong signals a dead ball, as the batsmen did not offer any shot.
Down the leg side, Matthew lets it go again. That was not far from the elbow.
Full toss now, MW misses out, flicking it straight to short mid-wicket.
A bouncer to finish, around leg, Wade ducks again.
Full and around middle, worked straight to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! A bit too straight. Angling onto the pads, Cummins is alert and tickles it to the fine leg fence.

FOUR! WHAM! The first real bad ball of the day. A short one, wide outside off, Cummins is up in a flash on seeing that and punches it through the covers. It is in the gap and races to the fence. Cummins moves to 13 now.
Full and straight, around off, pushed down the track.
Outside off, pushed straight to cover.
A bouncer to end the over, outside off, Pat sways away. So we are back to the Wagner-Wade duel.
Expectantly, a short ball, down the leg side, Wade offers no short and is hit on the left arm.
Full and around middle, watchfully defended.
A short ball, around middle and leg, Matthew looks to shoulder arms and is hit right on the bread basket!

Well bowled, well played! Wagner tests Wade's concentration with a full ball but the batsman is aware and ready. Flicks it towards fine leg for the first runs off Wagner this morning. The crowd cheers. So Wagner will now bowl to Cummins for the first time today.
A short ball to the all-rounder. Around leg, rising sharply, but Cummins does well to fend it down, well in front of short leg.

OUT! Caught down the leg side! Wagner gets the first wicket of the afternoon. In a way, it is good for Australia that Cummins is gone. They would not want their premier bowler to get injured to this short stuff. A length ball, outside leg, Pat looks to tickle but only manages a thin inside. Watling catches and appeals but PC is going nowhere. Now, he looks at the umpire who raises his finger and Cummins is happy to go. Wagner two away from a 5-fer in this innings.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! WHOOSH! Wade is looking forward to take on de Grandhomme. Full and wide outside off, Matthew reaches out and blasts it wide of mid off to the boundary at cover!
Outside off, left alone.
Around off, watchfully defended.
FOUR! Full and wide outside off, Wade reaches out and slashes hard. Gets a thick outside edge which flies over point to the fence. NO BALL signalled.

OUT! Caught! Wade is out of here. And, he is very, very distraught. A short ball, outside off, Matthew looks ready to punish it and pulls it really, really hard. But to his horror, he picks out Jeet Raval to perfection at deep mid-wicket! Surely, he did not want to get out this way? He takes some time and then trudges off.
Full and around middle, pushed down the ground.
Full ball, for a change from Wagner, outside leg, Starc misses his flick and is hit on the pads.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Around off, defended solidly.
Another one down the leg side, shorter as well, left alone.
Comes over the wickets, bowls it short, Mitchell looks to tuck it away and almost hits it into the hands of short leg. Just short and wide.
A short ball outside off, pulled wide of mid on for three runs. The lead is now 442.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! A length ball outside off, Starc just heaves it over mid off and clears the man. A bounce and into the fence.
Full and outside off, flayed through the covers for a single.
Down the leg side, Lyon misses his tuck and is hit on the box. Ouch.
Around off, pushed towards cover.
Full and around off, well blocked out.
FOUR! Heaved away! A length ball, around middle, Starc heaves it wide of short mid-wicket. There is no one down the ground. A boundary. 200 UP FOR AUSTRALIA, LEAD CROSSES 450.
FOUR! ADMONISHED! A short ball, around middle, Starc pulls it through mid-wicket. Consecutive boundaries. The tail-enders would be looking to have some fun.
Around middle and leg, tucked wide of short leg, towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
A length ball, around middle, defended towards silly point.
A short ball now, around leg, Nathan fens it down in front of short leg.

FOUR LEG BYES! Bizarre decision from umpire Nigel Llong. A few overs ago, he signalled a dead ball when Wade did not offer a shot. A similar case for Nathan Lyon, but this time, he has awarded runs to Australia. A short ball, down the leg side, Lyon looks to tuck but then shoulders arms. The ball hits his pads and trickles to the fine leg fence. The lead is now 460.
A short ball, outside off, pulled straight to short mid-wicket.
Outside off, a slash and a miss.
Outside off, Mitchell punches it towards cover where the fielder misfields due to extra bounce. A single taken off the deflection.
A down the leg side short leg side, tucked towards short leg.
A bouncer down the leg side, ducked under.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Back of a length ball down the leg side. Starc lets it be.
Another short ball down the leg side. Starc ducks under it.
FOUR! Top edge but Starc won't care. Another bouncer on middle, Starc looks to pull it away but gets a top edge which flies over the keeper and to the fence.
Slower yorker this time. Starc keeps it out nicely.
WIDE! Another bumper but line is wrong. Starc ducks under it. Watling collects it on the bounce. Called wide as it is way down the leg side.
Another bumper on middle, Starc pulls but has his eyes off the ball. Somehow manages to pull it towards square leg for a single.
In the channel outside off, Lyon pokes but gets beaten.

OUT! Caught at fly slip! Brilliant captaincy from Williamson to keep a fielder in that position. With Starc going after the balls so hard, edges flying through the slips are always on the cards. Exactly what happened. Fullish length ball outside off, Starc looks to power it over long off but gets a thick outside edge which goes straight to Taylor at fly slip who makes no mistake. Fifer for Southee. It's been a hard toil for the pacers and the Kiwi bowler kept coming hard and has got a fifer to his name.
Starc starts with a good length ball outside off, making it shape away just a hint. Raval lets it be.
Raval and New Zealand are underway! Starc bowls on the pads of the left-hander. Raval tucks it towards square leg and takes a singe.
Fullish length ball just outside off, left alone.
In the channel outside off again. Latham shoulders arms.

FOUR! Punched nicely! Fuller ball on middle and leg, Latham closes his bat face and punches it past diving sub fielder Neser at short mid-wicket. It races towards the long on fence. Neser gives it a chase but the ball wins the race. First boundary of the innings.
Shortish length ball just outside off, Latham rides the bounce and taps it towards the off side.

Huge appeal for caught behind but looks like it came off the pads. Cummins is right on the money first ball. Lands it on middle and leg, Raval looks to tuck it around but gets hit on the flap of his pad. The ball goes the slip cordon. Warner from gully comes ahead and takes the catch. The Aussies appeal but nothing from the umpire. The replays confirm no bat.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, angled in. Raval defends it out.
Good length ball outside off, Raval makes a leave.
Shortish length ball just outside off, Raval sways away form it.
That hit the crack and kept low! It is a fullish ball, the ones which are driveable. Raval is caught in two minds. As he first looks to drive but at the last moment draws his bat back.
Brilliant work from Head at short leg. A good length ball on the pads, Latham looks to tuck it towards square leg but Head moves to his left and stops it nicely.
In the channel outside off, Latham covers his stumps and lets it be. Carries to Paine at a perfect height behind the wicket.
Fuller and on off, Latham defends it towards mid off.
On middle, Latham pushes it towards mid on.
Landed on middle, Latham goes back and defends it out.
Bouncer on middle this time. Latham ducks under it to see off the over.
Good length ball outside off, Raval has his stumps covered as he shoulders arms.
Full and around off, Raval drives it well but cannot beat Wade at short extra cover.
This time Cummins lands it on off, Raval looks to defend but gets an outside edge.
Goes back to bowling in the corridor outside off. Raval lets it be.
Fullish but wide outside off, Raval makes another leave.
Full and on off, Raval defends it out solidly.
Back of a length ball on middle, Latham tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Shortish length ball outside off. Raval is not bothered as he shoulders arms.
Good length ball around off, Raval taps it towards cover.
Good length ball around off, Raval at the last moment taps it towards fourth slip.
Shortish and closer to off, Raval covers his stumps, drops his wrists and lets it be.
Another back of a length ball outside off, Raval lets it be. A few words from Starc to Raval there.
Outside off, left alone.
Around off, Latham is solid in his defense once again.

Wow! That kept low. We might get one sneak through. A good length ball on off, keeps very low. Latham does well to dig it out. Cummins smiles as looks at the spot where the ball pitched. Aiming to pitch there again?
No, not really as he goes short around off, Latham blocks it off the back foot.
Fullish this time and on off stump line, Latham is once again solid in the defense as he pushes it towards mid off.
Full and on the pads, Latham clips it towards the leg side nicely but Head makes another excellent stop at short leg.
Shortish length ball outside off, Raval lets it be.

OUT! Caught at point! Starc strikes and the poor run for Raval in Tests continues. Australia draw first blood. This is just behind the good length area but on off. Raval comes forward and looks to defend. The ball takes the outside edge and goes straight to Lyon at point. He is not going to drop these. Raval shakes his head as he walks off.
FOUR! Easily put away! Starc looks to welcome the Kiwi skipper with a yorker but ends up dishing a full toss on the pads. Williamson flicks it to the deep square leg fence to get off the mark.
FOUR! On the pads again from Starc. Williamson flicks it nicely through square leg to get another boundary. Starc is attempting an inswinging yorker but misses out.
Around off on a length, Williamson tucks it through gully to pick a couple.
Fuller length on off, Williamson defends it out. End of a successful over from Starc.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, watchfully patted down the track.
Around middle, tucked through short leg for a single.
Full and straight, swinging away, defended back to the bowler.

FOUR! ELEGANT! Williamson is off to a flier! His third boundary in just 6 balls faced. Full and outside off, Williamson leans and drives it through the covers. Interestingly, replays show that Williamson turned his bat in his hands before facing the ball.
Landed outside off, left alone.

Gone? Caught behind? Tim Paine starts to celebrate and then appeals but umpire Nigel Llong is unmoved. No review taken. Landed around off, Latham looks to defend but the ball moves away slightly and goes behind. Hard to pick any noise on first look or hear. Snickometer detects nothing when the ball goes past the bat.
Around off, Tom looks to defend but takes his bat inside the line.
Outside off, left alone again.
Full and straight, watchfully defended in front of mid on.
Landed outside off, slightly wider, let through once more.
Full and straight, pushed down the ground. Substitute Michael Neser gets across from short mid-wicket and stops the ball.

OUT! Turn and bounce, caught at short leg! That is a huge, huge wicket with 10 minutes to go to Lunch. Kane Williamson is gone. Nothing much he could have done there. The pitch has consumed him. Accurate Lyon lands this right on the rough outside off, around a shorter length. Williamson stays back to tuck but the ball lands on that black mark, generates dust and kicks off suddenly. Zooms in, takes the inside edge, hits the thigh and lobs to Matthew Wade at short leg. The Aussies celebrate and even before the appeal can be completed, Aleem Dar's finger is up. They check for the overstepping but Lyon is fine. Williamson walks back disappointed but to be fair, there was nothing much he could have done to that ball.
No hat-trick. Full and outside off, Taylor lunges and defends.
Full and outside off, watchfully played out again.
FOUR! Edged away! Full and wide outside off, Taylor reaches out to drive but gets a thick outside edge which flies behind backward point. Off the mark in streaky fashion.
Around off, blocked from the crease.
Full and around off, watchfully played out.
Down the leg side, left alone.
A length ball, around middle, Latham looks to flick but gets a leading edge towards cover. A single taken.
On a length, around off, Rosco looks to defend and then aims to take his bat away. Is late and gets beaten.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
In the air... safe! Landed around leg, Taylor looks to flick but the ball goes uppishly, wide of Marnus Labuschagne at leg gully. A single to fine leg. Wait a second. Leg bye signalled.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Around off, fuller in length, Taylor stays back and defends.
Oohh... full and outside off, Rosco looks to drive but the ball spins in and takes the inside edge onto the pads. Lobs up but is nowhere near first slip.
Tossed up outside off, RT drives it to the left of mid off and takes a single.
Short and outside off, cut behind point for a couple.
Full and on middle, Latham pushes this wide of substitute Michael Neser at mid on and pinches a quick run.
Landed outside off, Taylor shoulders arms and is hit on the thighs. Paine puts in a mild shout for LBW but is not entertained. LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Full and around off, bounces sharply but Latham is solid in defense.

Huge appeal for a caught behind! Turned down by umpire Llong. No warm-ups for Cummins. No looseners. He comes running in and lands it on a length outside off, making it to jag back in. Tom looks to defend but misses. The ball goes off something to the keeper and the slip cordon explodes. Llong is unmoved. Replays show that the ball hit the back thigh. Superb decision.

Huge appeal for LBW now! Turned down again! Will the Australians review? Cummins looks interested. Tim Paine walks towards Nathan Lyon at point to talk about the height and then does not take the review. A length ball outside off, hits a crack and stays a touch low. Latham is hit on his back foot and seems to fall over a touch. It looks close to the naked eye but Ball Tracker shows it to be going over the top. Superb decision from Nigel Llong and excellent call from Nathan Lyon at point to tell Paine not to review. He would have been at the best angle to see where the ball would have hit.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat. One run added to the total.
Outside off, on a length, Taylor looks to defend but then aims to take his bat away. Is late and the ball goes off the bottom edge, on the bounce, to gully.
On a length outside off, Rosco looks to defend but misses.
Flighted delivery outside off, Latham offers no shot to this one.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Tom defends it out.
Floated delivery on middle, TL defends it off the back foot.
Short delivery on off, Latham cuts it to point.
Flighted delivery on middle, well kept out again.
Short delivery on off, Latham makes room and cuts it through point. The batsmen get two runs.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Taylor looks to defend but misses it.
Outside off, Rosco offers no shot to this one.
Short delivery on leg, Taylor looks to pull but gets it off the glove. It goes towards fine leg for a run. That hurried onto Taylor.
On a good length on off, Latham defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Tom blocks it off the front foot.
Bowls a bouncer on leg, TL does well to duck under it.
Floated delivery on middle, Taylor flicks it to short fine leg.
Tossed up delivery on off, Rosco defends it back towards the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Ross flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Loopy delivery on off, Tom blocks it well.
Floated delivery on middle, Latham flicks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
FOUR! Nice shot. Tossed up delivery on middle, Taylor plays a slog sweep over mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a good length on middle, Latham nudges it towards the leg side.
Good length delivery on off, Tom defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, TL leaves it alone.
Bowls a bumper, Latham ducks under it.
Another LBW appeal but turned down. On a good length on leg, Latham looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Latham looks to defend but misses it.
Full and around off, worked in front of short leg.
Full and outside off, Rosco looks to defend but gets a bottom edge, on the bounce over the keeper to first slip.

FOUR! AUDACIOUS! Taylor is ready for the challenge. Flighted outside off, Rosco gets down and mows the slog sweep. There is a deep square leg in place but this is played in front of him, towards mid-wicket.
Floated delivery on off, Taylor sweeps it through mid-wicket for a run.
Loopy delivery on off, Latham keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Latham defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Taylor defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on off, Taylor plays it to covers.
Length delivery on middle, Ross flicks it through square leg. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Short of a length delivery outside off, Taylor looks to pull but misses it.
WIDE! A wild bouncer, around middle and leg, comfortably ducked under. It is not even a proper duck. The bouncer was so high.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery! On a good length and outside off, Rosco looks to defend but the ball pitches and then seams away, to beat the outside edge.
Good length delivery on off, Ross defends it off the front foot.
The arm ball outside off, left alone.
Flighted delivery on middle, Latham blocks it off the front foot.

Oohhh... a bit too early. Floated delivery on middle, Latham comes down the track and looks to flick but is beaten in flight. Luckily for him, the ball hits his pads. Lyon spotted pretty early that Latham was off his blocks. Hence, fired it in.
Loopy delivery on middle, Tom looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Short delivery outside off, Latham cuts it to point.
Flighted delivery on middle, Latham keeps it out.
Full delivery on middle, Taylor defends it to mid-wicket.
Rash shot. On a good length on off, Taylor looks to drive, without moving his feet and gets a bottom edge, which goes on the bounce to the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, Ross defends it off the back foot.

Full delivery outside off, Taylor drives it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs. Good running between the wickets. 50 UP FOR NEW ZEALAND.
On a length on middle, Latham flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
On a good length on middle, Latham looks to flick but gets it off the inner half of the bat. It goes towards fine leg for a single.
Short delivery on middle, Latham looks to pull but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

That is fired down the leg side. 92.5 kph, Latham looks to sweep but misses it. Tim Paine behind just about manages to get his glove to stop that. Immediately wrings his hands in pain. That would have hurt.
Tossed up delivery on off, Latham plays that very late and guides it towards short third man. The batsmen take a run.
Flighted delivery on off, Taylor defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on off, Taylor looks to play a reverse sweep but misses it and gets hit on the boot.
Full delivery on middle, Taylor drives it through mid on for a run.

Short of a length delivery on middle, Taylor pulls it towards mid-wicket where the fielder makes a fine stop.
Bowls it down the leg side, Taylor lets it go.

OUT! Caught behind! There goes Rosco. Starc has struck. His second wicket. Taylor, looking to play his natural game, has perished. The ball is not much different from the second one in this over. The length is short and Rosco thinks that he can pull across the line. He does so but perhaps this one comes quicker than his anticipation. Takes the under edge and goes behind, with Tim Paine completing the formalities. Another massive blow.
Around middle, pushed towards short mid-wicket.
Outside off, played straight to point.

OUT! LBW! That is plumb and Aleem Dar has to overturn the decision! Lyon has his second. The arm ball does the trick. Pitched around off, Latham stays back to defend but misses it as the ball skids off the deck. He is caught in his crease and is hit on the pads. Lyon immediately roars but umpire Dar shakes his head. Tim Paine has a long chat with his bowler and when it seems like both are not convinced whether that would be out, he signals for the review. Ball Tracker shows it to be hitting leg stump and one man who could have stayed for hours at the crease, departs.
Full and outside off, Watling dead-bats it.
Down the leg side, helped towards square leg.
Outside off, BJ hangs back to defend.
Length delivery on middle, Nicholls flicks it through square leg. Lyon runs and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
FOUR! What a shot! Full delivery on leg, Watling flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Watling sways away from it.
Full delivery on off, Watling drives it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Outside off, Watling offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on middle, Watling defends it off the back foot.
Around off, blocked from the crease.
Outside off, played towards point.
FOUR! A rare boundary. You need to punish the bad balls. Short and outside off, Nicholls rocks back and pulls it through mid-wicket.
Landed outside off, the arm ball, left alone.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Full and around off, Nicholls lunges and blocks it down the track.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
FOUR! Landed outside off, Watling looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge, along the ground, past second slip towards third man.

ON THE HELMET! First up, Watling is okay and signals a thumbs up. That just kept on rising. On a length outside off, Watling looks to defend but the ball suddenly kicks up, goes past his gloves and hits him on the grille of his helmet. He walks away immediately and when Cummins asks about his health, he indicates he is fine.

Very good bowling. Cummins understands that Watling would be expecting a short ball, so bowls it fuller. BJ is late in bringing his bat down to defend and is beaten, with the ball moving away late to beat the outside edge, almost like a leg spinner.
Similar line and length, this time BJW is perfect in his forward defense.
Landed outside off, dabbed towards gully.
A short ball outside off, Nicholls looks to pull but misses. Paine fumbles behind.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Landed outside off, punched towards cover.
That is a very good stop. Around off, Nicholls tucks it through the leg side but Matthew Wade at short leg does well to stop it.
Gets it past Wade this time for a run.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Landed outside off, watchfully defended towards cover.
Around off, pushed towards cover.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Too full and a bit too straight. Nicholls flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple. Moves to 10 and the stand is worth 20 from 33 balls.

EDGED, BUT DOES NOT CARRY! Paine smiles. Perfect from Cummins, landing it on a length outside off and drawing Nicholls forward. The outside edge is induced but for some reason it lands in front of Tim Paine.
FOUR! A rare bad ball. Short and outside off, Watling rocks back and cuts it through the covers.
Around off, solidly defended.
This time he is on his back foot to defend.

Full and around middle, Watling lunges and flicks it towards the leg side. Matthew Wade at short leg dives to his left and flicks it immediately at the stumps. Tim Paine misses it but Steven Smith at first slip stops it. Wade apologizes to his skipper.
Outside off, driven straight to mid off.

Loopy delivery on off, Nicholls looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. Tim Paine has a chat with his bowler who straightaway indicates there was an inside edge on that one. Replays confirm.
Full and outside off, driven beautifully but straight back to Cummins who deflects it to mid off off his left hand.

Flighted delivery on off, Nicholls plays it to covers.

Around middle, worked through mid-wicket for a single.

Flighted delivery on middle, Nicholls plays it to point.
Loopy delivery on off, Henry plays it towards point.
Full and outside off, solidly defended in front of silly point.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Landed outside off, hint of away turn, but a bit too short. Punched through the covers for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Nicholls plays it to mid on.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Nicholls looks to defend but gets an inside edge. It goes on a bounce to short leg.

OUT! CAUGHT! Well, a bit of a bizarre procedure there. Let us describe the events one by one. Tossed up delivery outside off, Nicholls lunges to defend but the ball comes in with the angle, hits the pads and lobs to silly point. Now, Travis Head takes it, celebrates and then appeals. Aleem Dar immediately raises his finger. Seeing that, Travis Head runs around in circles in jubilation while Nicholls asks the umpire the manner of his dismissal. On being informed that he has been given out caught, Nicholls has a long chat with Watling and then signals the 'T'. Now comes the bizarre part. From one side of the replays, it seems that the ball has hit the pad, then hit the back of the bat and dipped to Travis Head who has taken a very good catch, inches above the ground. But the third umpire is only checking the legality of the catch. Does that mean he is satisfied there is an edge? No Hot Spot is checked, nor Snicko. Eventually, the third umpire relays the message to Aleem Dar who signals it OUT once again. So - was this an umpire's review or a player's review? Something to ponder as TEA IS TAKEN.
Flighted delivery on off, de Grandhomme defends it to covers off the back foot.
SIX! Amazing shot. Flighted delivery on middle, de Grandhomme comes down the track and lofts it over wide long on for a maximum.
On a good length on off, Watling defends it off the front foot.

Bowls a bouncer, Watling ducks under it.

Huge appeal for a caught behind! Turned down by Aleem Dar. Tossed up outside off, Watling lunges to defend but misses. Tim Paine fumbles but takes it in the second attempt. There is a noise and up go the Aussies but Dar shakes his head. Paine is not sure whether there was an outside edge and does not take the review. Hot Spot detects a mark when the ball passes the bat! Reviews and Tim...a pain for Australia.

Was that a drop? Looking at Matthew Wade's reaction, it seems so. Around middle, Watling looked to flick and hit it very hard. The ball seemed to go flush onto Matthew Wade's right shoulder and deflected away. Smith pats Wade on his head.
On a good length on middle, de Grandhomme looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.

Oops! Watch out! Plenty of drama on this ball. A length ball, around middle, de Grandhomme looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and hits him on the pads. The ball rolls away and de Grandhomme thinks about the single but is sent back. He lazily stands there and in the meanwhile, Matthew Wade charges in from short leg. Also, Nathan Lyon comes in running from point. Wade tries to kick the ball onto the stumps at the striker's end with his left foot but cannot quite connect cleanly. De Grandhomme would have been out had that hit! But the fun does not end there. Wade and Lyon almost collide into one another, knocking each other down! Both get up with a smile while umpire Aleem Dar at square leg has a chuckle.

GLOVED, BUT WIDE OF SHORT LEG! A nasty bouncer, around middle, Colin leaps to fend but the ball keeps on rising. Takes the glove and flies in the air, but is well wide of short leg, en route fine leg. A single taken.
On a good length outside off, coming in, Watling looks to defend but misses and is hit on the pads.

The ball flies in the air but is well wide of the man at deep mid-wicket. Lands around deep backward square leg and trickles into the fence.

EDGED, DROPPED! A tough chance. Full and outside off, Watling looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies towards Steven Smith at first slip but he is wrong-footed. Goes to his right and the ball is to his left. He is not able to react and the strawberry hits his left palm and goes down. Two runs taken.

50-RUN STAND UP. Finally, some fight from New Zealand. Length delivery on middle, Watling looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards square leg. The batsmen take a single. The umpire gives it as a leg bye. 50-run stand is up between BJ Watling and Colin de Grandhomme.

OUT! Edged and taken! Smith put one down earlier but he makes amends for that by taking a pretty decent catch. The batsman is different though. Colin de Grandhomme's wonderful fight ends. Much similar to the dismissal of Joe Burns on Saturday evening. Not exactly a brute but a toughie nevertheless. A length ball around off, de Grandhomme is forced to play at it but the ball seams away off the deck and takes Colin by surprise. He cannot do much having already committed into the shot. The outside edge is taken and it goes low to first slip where Steven Smith takes it safely, then dives forward. End of a wonderful 56-run stand.
A length ball, around off, defended solidly in front of short leg and silly point, right onto the middle of the pitch.
A short ball, down the leg side, left alone. There is a leg gully in place.
OUCH! Did he pick that? Doesn't seem so. A short ball, around off, coming in with the angle, Santner stays back to fend at it but the ball hits his chest, then his neck and drops down.

OUT! There is a faint mark on Hot Spot and Watling is caught down the leg side! A very bizarre moment for Australia. A short ball down the leg side, Watling got across and looked to fend but seemed to have missed. Now, there was a noise. Paine heard it. Or he looked to be the only one who heard it. He straightaway ran to the bowler in celebration and then started to appeal. But umpire Nigel Llong, seemingly looking frustrated at the continuous appeals from Australia all day, shook his head. For a change, Paine did not ask anyone. ANYONE. Smith at first slip did not move an inch while Starc was just looking to go back to his mark. Then suddenly, he sees his skipper go for the review and is clearly surprised, asking him whether he was sure! From the replays, to the naked eye, it looks the ball has hit the abdomen. But Hot Spot shows the tiniest of marks on the glove and then the abdomen! Nothing on the Snickometer but that does not matter. The decision is overturned and Watling has to depart. Well played, once again.
Short of a length delivery down the leg side, Santner leaves it alone.

OUT! That is a stunning catch! The short stuff gets Santner. He was never looking comfortable and departs for a 8-ball duck. But what concentration from Travis Head! It is never easy to field for a fast bowler but Head did not move an inch. Normally, players take their eyes off and look for cover. But not Head. A short ball, right at the body from around the wicket, Mitchell cannot do much other than hop and tamely fend at it. The ball goes straight off the face of the bat, straight to silly point who just takes it calmly. Or makes it look pretty simple.

OUT! Caught behind and Starc has 9 in the match! A length ball, around middle, Wagner looks to defend but the ball angles away, takes the outside edge and goes to Tim Paine. Starc starts to celebrate and is that the end of the game? Will Lockie Ferguson come out to bat?
Short delivery on leg, Southee flicks it uppishly towards mid-wicket. It lands safely in no man's land. The batsmen take a single.

Full delivery on middle, Southee flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.

Length delivery on off, Southee plays it towards covers for a single.

Around off, pushed down the ground.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Starc does not get a 10-fer. We do not have a Day 5. Lyon finishes things off. Full and outside off, Southee comes forward to defend but the ball spins in slightly, takes the outside edge and goes straight to first slip. An easy chance for Steven Smith this time and he makes no mistake. AUSTRALIA WIN BY 296 RUNS!
